content: Couldn't put it down, really interesting stories and characters. And the game went way longer than similar games on mobile and the plot was way richer and well developed than usual. The puzzles are engaging and balanced.
Too short :b

One of my absolute favorite mobile games of all time just about up there with the likes of "Might and Magic: Clash of Heroes," both in quality and ALMOST similar genre. 5 stars without even having to think about it. I really hope we see another game from these guys as they have obvious talent. Keep up the good work guys, and PLEASE....give us more!
Great
So cool game

A touch on the easy side but that is not always bad thing. I adore the characters and the world. Would love to see more of them. Gameplay is original but works better on tablet than phone. I hope we see more of these charscters and originality from robit circus.

Man one of the best games I have played in a while. Not to challenging but still has it's difficulties. The story makes this game worth playing. Very original game play definitely worth what you pay for it.
Mix and of old fallout and rpg

A highly enjoyable experience. Definitely worth try, you can really feel all effort and dedication that creators and developers put in it. Maybe the best game of it's genre, in my modest opinion. Good story plot and twists, lot's of primary and secondary missions. Easy controls and gameplay. Excellent time killer. A well earned FIVE STARS game !
Runs smoothly! One of the best turn based strategy games on Android

An interesting mix of 'run the path' and tactical rpg. Some battles can be surprisingly tough without intelligent movement, character selection and customization, and ability usage. Quite a bit of customization and a reasonably engaging wasteland-punk story.
Man, this game is really good. It seems like a pretty straightforward turn-based strategy game, but there are some pretty interesting twists that really separate it from the pack. Give it a shot.
Boring, couldn't force myself to play beyond ~6th mission.
A really fun and strategic game :D Didn't expect to be able to trick robots into blowing up their allies. Muhaha >:) Experiencing no ads and no hidden bp2w features. That's really refreshing!
the story is great, but for a card's game it feels more like a puzzle and the skills system is not really nice
Would of been enjoyable if not for the objectives. Why not just let us play our way?
I guess it's fun. It oozes ideology.

I really loved this game. Its challenging without being frustrating, it's beautiful, and the story is compelling. I particularly liked the fact that Rose ponders and is shaken after she makes her first kill. You don't see that very often in games and it was refreshing.

This game perfectly meshes aspects of some of my favorite genres, including turn-based RPG and strategy, and packages it in a compelling post-apocalyptic world with an engaging storyline. The game has a perfect learning curve: You'll be up and running in no time, and you'll discover greater strategies and combos along the way as you unlock more powers and weapons and face new foes and obstacles. Also nice: The ability to easily redistribute certain assigned resources.
I never seen this type of gameplay before and I really really like it
The story is nice and the gameplay challenges you to make the best strategy.But which grids come for your advantage are pure luck, sometimes you need to restart a battle just because of this
Great game with excellent mechanics, interface and story. Easy to play on phone as text and buttons all big enough. Really enjoying still after several chapters.
Not balanced. Strict line story. Can't choose character to play main/side missions. Waste of money.
Excellent
Lots of fun!
Spawning enemies on early levels - not a good move
This game is massively underpriced. Great mechanics and awesome visuals. Wouldn't hesitate to buy this even if it costs $5.

First of all I liked the game and it saddens me that I can only give this 3/5. Whilst the graphics, story elements and (at times) the gameplay are great this title suffers immensely from the random grid layouts. There were many times I got screwed over by the grid and had to keep restarting missions till I got the luck needed to win. It can feel cheap and undeserved to win and annoying and frustrating to lose. Overall still enjoy it but please remove the randomness!
It has been a long time since I played a game with no adds not in app purchases. This one has neither. I also really like the game itself.
Great game, no ads, no microtransactions.
First game off Gamepass, just finished the story, great game

Since I like stories. I always just go "when does this end" - because I wanna see the ending. All in all great story and great combat. Gets easier halfway with all the unlockables. I played this game straight for 3 to 4 days and loved it When the ending came... I really wished for a part 2.
Great game. Affordable price. A rare find in mobile gaming.
Huge game, deep gameplay and brilliant story.
Best phone game I've played, really hoping for a sequel
Great combo of role playing, puzzle and strategy!
Great story, mid level graphics and gameplay. One of the more imersive games I've played on the phone
Awesome game. Great gameplay and story and lots of content too. Loved it!!
Having a lot of fun! Perfect mix of pickup and play and continuous action!

I loved it. The story is basic but the characters are likeable. The gameplay loop never got stale The environments were extremely well made I put in 16 hours in it! Way more than I've had with any recent mobile game I've played
This game is AMAZING. Never have I played a turn based game that was so intense!

Definitely one of the better story based games I have played on mobile. It will keep you engaged for quite a while. Story is great, the difficulty needs a bit of polishing. But otherwise must try for the price!
Interesting story and fun gameplay.
Great gane, with very good combat mechanics, and very entertaining story. One of the best i played on android
This game is really fun. I didn't expect it to be so enjoyable. Really recommend it.
Best game ever made! You just gotta try it. Perfect 5/5 stars!

Loved the concept as well as the gameplay. It made me keep playing and made me to complete the game as soon as possible so that to reach the end of the story. Storyline was interesting. Loved the graphics of the game. Can play for hours without being bored.
Decievingly deep
Perfect balance of gameplay, story, visuals and a pinch of puzzler spice! Loot would be nice but that's just personal preference
Figuring out a good strategy method was a bit confusing at first, but once you get the hang of it, it's addicting. Fun game.
Fully enjoyed this hope more follow
The game is so much fun. The mechanics of gameplay and how smoothly it plays is awesome. The story wasn't to my liking but didn't hurt the experience. Congratulations to the developers.

Runs amazing on tablet and Chromebook. No scummy microtransactions or ads. So refreshing to see a proper game like this. Very well designed, great music, great graphics, great progression and a lot of content. Think I will be playing this for some time yet!

Super fun! I'm picky about my games, this one has a really engaging story, characters, puzzle aspect... I love the feel of it and the interaction between the characters. I'd get more games from this team.
This game was a fantastic experience. It had a great story, and the gameplay was great.
Nice puzzle action game
For a tactical game, a lot relies on luck. If you're given a bad layout from the start, you might as well reset the mission and try again.
Incredibly good game. A nuanced and engaging storyline, novel and fun gameplay, and stylish graphics. What more could you ask for? Can't wait for the sequel that had BETTER be on its way!

Astounding game. Seriously. Couldn't be more happy with this game. From the story to the gameplay to sound to graphics, it's all top notch. It feels easy to just give out five stars across the board, but this game truly deserves it. I waited til beating the whole thing before rating it as I wanted my review to be all-encompassing. My takeaway? Download it and play this. Do it now. Stop reading. Do it.
Great game! The story telling, game control and challenge are well balanced.
Nice story, great mechanics, recommended
Fun game with a good story, highly recommended
NEEDS a dictionary.

Was fairly happy with the game a little disappointed with the ending thus the 4 and not 5 stars. Also some tips were not needed so much as others that didn't even get disclosed i had to find out myself after almost beating the game.

Flawless, for what it does, so if you like story- and character-rich puzzle-based RPGs, this is your game This part is directed to the devs: accomplishments are munged. "Defeat 200 enemies", "Defeat 500 enemies" and "Defeat 1000 enemies" are each hanging at 99% complete
Solid gameplay
Good storyline and fun fighting strategies
Fun quick tactics game
Nice gameplay and engaging story, definitely recommend!
It's...okish? They tried to make a game, and they did. Good job? It's certainly not terrible, it's certainly not great.

Game is very enjoyable with interesting mechanics and engaging gameplay. With some quality of life fixes it would be a 5 star game. Can be difficult to deselect a path when deciding routes, for example.
One of the few games I've played right through and gone to look for more from the developers. Original game play, plus good story and design makes for a really good game.
This is what mobile gaming is all about. Simple one finger swiping mechanics and a comic-like story to keep you engage.
Love this game. Love the storyline.

It gave me few hours of enjoyment so thank you very much for this. Unfortunately I feel that playing more of this will be waste of my time. The story is flat and clich√© bu honestly I would not care if the gameplay was good. I feel that there was very little effort put in the design of the core of the gameplay. The battles are repititve, a lot is based on chance of how the tiles would turn out and there is not much player control. Its a boring grind with no interesting situations.
It's fun and has some depth to it.

Best game I have ever played!!! I was sad when I finished the story, a kind of emptiness that you feel when you binge something so good ( like the Harry Potter series or the game Last of Us). I even pushed to complete the game for 1 month xD Anyways, I do recommend this game!
Great graphic and gameplay style.
The gameplay is nicely balanced between challenging and rewarding, the story is surprisingly moving, and the visuals are great! Get this game!!!
The gameplay is not my normal type but it never got boring, the designs are fun and interesting, but the real pull for this is the story and characters. I would recommend this to anyone interested.

i dont think its a bad game,it has clean art style and good sound track but the game play loop is kinda boring, i finish the game and feel unsatisfied. the ability is kinda imbalance consider some ability is cheap but op and some ability is hella expensive but useless. The nitrium farming buggeds me considering it need to play the same map again and again, the story is mediocre and the bonus objective just keep repeating without any new form of ovjective.

Very good game and concept...but limited game options other than movement and hit strategy...seems repititive...but overall good game to play...and pricing is awesome...story cut scenes could have been short

The game has been surprisingly fun for the short time I have had it. On the negative side I have been asked for a rating four times and I haven't even had the game a full day and there are some moments of lag when picking menu choices but overall I am very pleased with my purchase. Worth every penny.
Lots of fun! Took me some time to get into it and by then I couldn't stop! Fun story, an excellent game from start to finish.
super fun !
Nice graphics. Gameplay was slightly blah to begin with and the random tile color changing during combat turns was kind of annoying and gave the combat too much of a luck feel to it.
Innovative and fun!
Unbelivable addicting.. and challanging too.sarishfied
The most shity game ever...total waste of money
Unique, fun turn-based strategy story...Haven't been this hooked on a game for a while
Really cool so far. Adds a new concept and do far it's kinda cool. Would definitely recommend
First mobile game I've finished perhaps ever? Just fantastic. Worked great on a cheap old Android.

I'll be honest, I thought I was going to hate this game because I don't enjoy "match 3" style games. Honestly, I'm addicted to it now. Good story, fun and strategic game play, great artwork, challenge, character building... it has it all. So much fun. Earned my 5 stars.

I don't often bother giving positive reviews but I had to for this game. I've been looking for something new to play and got the game pass. I downloaded several games, played them a few minutes and deleted them. But this game held my attention. It's got a decent story and character development. Would recommend to all who like turned based RPG games.
One of the best Android games I've played, with a fun mechanic and a pretty compelling story.
Perfection

This is a genuinely excellent game that was built for mobile, but is as deep and engaging as any "real" game. It combines a simple match-the-colours puzzle concept with surprisingly deep rpg progression and XCom style strategic combat. Even more surprising is the story, which is at first seemingly shallow, but becomes quite engaging and satisfying. Can't recommend highly enough and looking forward to more from this dev!
A lot of effort into keeping the characters and the story interesting (and diverse!). The game play is simple to pick up and challenging enough to keep you playing.
I very very rarely review games and apps but this is absolute fire. Well worth the money
I love the storyline and graphic, and most importantly the game-play. The Grids! The variety of Justice Powers enable us to combine the ultimate one for each battle. I just wish there's part 2, üòÄ

Hugely enjoyable. Not sure I've spent so much time getting everything I can out of a mobile game. The gameplay was rewarding and I felt unique, the story was excellent and the graphics made me a joy. I'm a fam of the game and will follow the developers new games intently.
I had fun. Good story. Fun Play.
Great game. Nice story, good mechanics and amazing concept.

I love offline turn-based rpg. This game gives me a new whole gameplay. So enjoyable. But I think you still have minor bugs. When I was equipped with a weapon n I bought a new one. The one I equipped was just gone, with the gem attached to it. You made no inventory system, I've got it, but at least you could give us back the credits. Trying to drag the line also somehow a bit tricky, but the zoom feature helped a bit. Good game, with a great gameplay, goodjob
Unique combat system, engaging story, funny characters... This is the most fun I've had playing a game in a very long time!

Fun and challenging tactical strategy RPG, tailor-made for Mobile devices. I was looking for an experience similar to XCom and found this instead: A game that can easily stand on its own with unique game design and a cool story to round it off. Give it a go if you like turn-based tactical strategy gameplay for a few rounds on the go.
Solid game. Great look, great mechanics, great characters, great story. I'd gladly pay $5 for every mobile game if they were this good.

It's hard to overrate this game. I guess it's technically and arcade style, but there is a lot of strategy and customization. The storyline is gripping. The gameplay is dynamic and progressive in a way that makes you want to keep at it all day. I highly recommend this as a top tier mobile game.

This is a great game. The turn based nature combined with your matching is a great combination. The story is deep enough to be engaging but doesn't stay more than its welcome which is perfect. The game progresses well by introducing new challenges and giving new options for strategy without it becoming some kind of level up to do the same thing but does more damage like RPGs tend to be nowadays. Awesome work, hats off to the team.
Not my bag. I enjoyed playing as the ranged class but the melee class quickly became tedious. Stopped enjoying the game when forced to switch back to the melee class and uninstalled.
Great plot, awesome mechanics, electrifying music - six stars :)

Great game, could be way better though. Mechanics are very good. Storyline is very good. Dialogues feel like they've been written by a teenager, and they take away from the story and quality. Weapons feel like an unfinished concept, same with shards. Game becomes unbalanced about halfway through, does not scale difficulty to the character development levels. AI has some basic flaws, like attacking characters that are invulnerable. Ending was underwhelming, that's probably my biggest gripe.
Fun game. Could use balancing towards act 3 and 4. Was very easy. Also an endless tournament mode for high end characters would be appreciated.
Easy to learn, cool game mechanics. Nice graphics and story too.

Only 2... Why:The game will not save your place if you have to close and return. Had to pay before I sampled. Graphics are really good but sometimes hard to operate. But there is option to confirm move in settingsüòâ. Story is interesting but really hard to follow. I'm guessing this is a PC game not a cell game? IDK. It's OK but annoying in waysüòï after playing it I found the balance to be off and ability to earn $ To be able to stay in the fight impossible to get. Grinding for little coin üôÑ
Very good concept and a novel gameplay experience. Full stars for effort and story and characterization.

Really cool game. I'm a fan of Civilization, Heroes of Might and Magic, etc. The game has a depth of play you really don't get until missions become harder. I glossed over any tutorial elements and am now stuck on a mission I am unable to beat because of poor weapon choice. May have to restart but I don't mind. It's fun.
This game is amazing!! I love the art and the story line, the only thing that made me upset is that I finished it üòÇ
worth every dollar ü§ë greaty story great progrssion pacing for upgrades great mechanics

Frustrating and unrewarding. After just a few introductory levels, the game gets so hard it gets to the point of hit and miss. The luck element cancels the strategy element and leaves you frustrated and ultimately unrewarded when you finally win because you got lucky with the tiles. Shame because the story and the graphics could have made this so much more. Even the developers advise you to set the difficulty level to rookie but lowering difficulty is just a slap in the face.

So much better than I expected! This game was supposed to be a fun kind of puzzley game, but wow what a compelling story. None of the characters were shallowly written, and it was challenging enough to stay engaged without being so hard I gave up altogether before finishing it. I almost never finish games
Very addictive
Good game. I don't love the art style and the controls can be a little tricky but fun nonetheless.
Great comic book atmosphere, more nuanced tactics than expected. On Play Pass so can't comment on fairness of economics but this is a legit fun game.

So-so. Very poor story line. You have three heroes (I had) but lot's of missions allow you to take only two. Why? Maybe there more heroes ahead but too borring to find this out. You can easily pack two guys like tanks and drive your way. Balance Vs tactics: I would say 50/50. In many cases you ran as far as you can and hit somebody. This is not the Game. Some sort of time killer. Hints to developers: Add arrows where next enemy will appear. Rebuild list of skill. Weapons should have some unique
Great game with an engaging story line, character customization, and unique combat system. A fun, casual puzzle rpg.
One of the few mobile games that feels like a real game.
This is an awesome game which has completely gripped me! The puzzle play is perfect and I love the story. Top notch!
Very good game, solid story, awesome art and sounds, nice game play. Maybe a bit repetitive toward the end but the story is good enough to keep you playing. Highly recommended!

This is a FANTASTIC puzzle RPG. The core mechanic is simple, but the levels have enough varied goals and obstacles to keep it interesting. The story is pretty good and the dialog is amusing and moving in turns. This is one of my favorite mobile games of all time.
Absolutely awesome mobile game! A great story and fun way to play, this game had me hooked. Hoping for the sequel to come out soon!
Great game If it had voice acting... I'd give 10 stars!
This game is amazing. I want more.

As a mobile game, at a mobile price, this is a decent title for the time spent. On the other hand...-2 stars for three reasons. 1. The core fight /matching system is fine, but everything else suffers under a mountain of click-through. 2. Shallow "progressive" narrative, which somehow missed the opportunity to include some token ethnicity. 3. Trivial story, motivation, resolution. Only one character really develops. Everyone else, good or bad, stays that way. The ending is a thing.
Very fun and challenging game. Well worth $5
Beautiful game, a great time to spend your time in a fascinating and engaging world .
Awesome battle system and good story
Fun little game. It's nice to just pay once and play.. puzzles have enough challenge to stay engaging so far.
Extremely well designed!

This game is so good. I bought it a few months ago and shelved it after like two or three levels, because I assumed it was just "walk the longest path, do damage, repeat". Well I played it again recently and I couldn't be more wrong. The game gets much harder quick, and with skills and different enemy types you really gotta take a second to decide on your path otherwise you can get surrounded and trapped. It's fun, and with the art style and sfx it's satisfying to crush a final blow to enemies
Great puzzle combo game with rpg mechanics and intriguing storyline. Must play!
Doesnt even initiated on my device. Waste of time to download.
Wow
Great game and good story line
Engaging story, fun game play, and inventive mechanics. What more could you want?
Very cool puzzle shooter.. also a nice story to drive the action.

This I believe is the second or third game I've given five stars. The story is just phenomenal. I think devs forget how crucial is to hook the player. The gameplay is also great with enough customization to keep you interested all game. This is not as hard as some people have made it out to be. If you play the side missions you shouldn't be stuck for long. Excellent game, hoping for a sequelü§û. Rare find among the drudges of mobile games.
Beautiful Game
Amazing game. It's the only one I've played all the way through. Has a comic book dialogue that I love. 5/5 would recommend to any of my puzzle gamer friends
Bought this on Steam but am I glad this made its way to Android

Why can't we have more games like this on the Android platform? Whill I don't have the same sentiments as other reviewers on here claiming that it's the best game on earth, it is a pretty good game. It is highly worth the price and fun to boot. At times the storyline dialog can be a bit hoaky but for the most part it's pretty good. The gameplay is great and I honestly believe you wouldn't go wrong buying this game. It's a rare treat to find something on this OS worth playing.
This is one of the best games I have ever played for mobile. Everything from the art style, to the storyline, to the unique gameplay just makes this perfect.
Love it. Fairly simple tile matching gaming. With good graphics a decent story, and great character/world design
It's pretty fun. Sometimes a bad seed for a level can hurt when you're low level, but it's fun to play and requires at least little strategy.
A great game with solid story and well written characters. If anything it makes me sad that there aren't more games like this for mobile
Game is awesome. Great story. Tactical and difficult combat. Good characters. Its also it's on play pass so if you have that no reason to not get this gem
The puzzle mixed with strategy is challenging and fun. Hands down, one of the best games out there.
Definitely the highest quality mobile game I've ever played.
Addicted
It takes a little getting used to. Great story and great game play.
This is the best game on this platform. I love this game..
Love it great story line addicted.

Do you like turn based tactical gameplay? Do you like role playing games with engaging characters? Do you like puzzle games? If you answered yes to any of those questions, you should give this game a try. Engaging, customizable characters. Different combinations of characters and powers lend good replay value. The missions have enough interesting mechanics to keep things fresh without feeling gimmicky. Excellently balanced game with a decent level of challenge.
Addicting tile based strategy game. Definitely has a comic book/anime vibe, which I really like. Not to mention there are no micro transactions. This game is definitely a diamond in the rough.
This is a super fun game. Definetly worth the price. Ive played for about an hour and the puzzles are fun and the combat is simple but effective!
Lovely lil storyline and very addicting.
I don't give out 5 stars very often but this game has earned it. It's fun, unique, uses my brain, and has an interesting story.
Honestly super impressed with this one! Plays fast, puzzle is great, fun story and cool graphics, plus no ads or intrusive bs... Really feel like i got my money's worth. Thanks devs!
I loved loved loved the game. I loved the story line; the simplicity of play. Unfortunately, it was over way to quickly!
LOVE Ticket to Earth!!! Thank you Google Play Pass!!! Definitely worth the worth $4.99 if you do not have Google Play Pass. NO in-game purchase Amazing!!! Awesome RPG game play turn base game.
Great game. One of best with playpass.
One of the best mobile games I've played! Combat is challenging but rewarding. The characters and story are highly enjoyable! Totally worth the money for hours of entertainment.
Absolutely flawless. Good value, no bugs or glitches, very appealing graphic design. They also put a lot of love into the storytelling. Thumbs up!
This game is awesome!!! Fun, interesting story, great graphics. It is the perfect game so far!!!
The concept is really out of left field and it works. Interesting setting and story as well.
Please make more games u guys are great developers.... Loved the game
Really engaging and you can skip the cut scenes. Well done, fun.
Excellent game. Didn't expect it. The other reviews are right. Very special game with innovative super addictive gameplay.

Very well thought out game. A good playing principle (sometimes a bit difficult interface e.g. when you want to get info on the ennemies on the board), really enjoyable playing experience. And the story is good, loved the few references to the Australian political landscape! Well done!
Great game
Great tactical RPG. Worth it. Original, good gameplay.
Brilliant... Waiting for the next one
Great game, it's a lot of fun and well worth the money spent.
After one week of playing and on the final stage they ask me to pay to continue to play.

This is the only mobile RPG that actually qualifies as an RPG. Best mobile game I've ever played. Hell maybe even one of the best games in general when you consider I have a strong bias against mobile games in general. Well worth the 5 dollars.
What a gem. Best mobile game experience ive had.
indieeeee supportttt!!!
Interesting turn based game with strong puzzle dynamic.
Great game, very enjoyable. Lots of different styles of game play. Loved the story line. Graphics and art work is amazing. Download this game and be very entertained for weeks.
Great mechanic for a mobile rpg. It's like bejeweled meets final fantasy

Great graphics and story line! Unique combat system keeps each battle engaging. Needs a little more find tuning in balancing in difficulty and character skills but that doesn't distract from the game much.
The best android game I have ever played, after Call of Duty Mobile...
Fun mix of puzzle and a turn based rpg
Ticket to Earth is a refreshing playing experience that is a simple balance of strategy and story. Very well done!

Felt bad only paying 20 cents for this. Stunning tile-connecting SRPG hybrid. Upgrading abilities can be grindy, but there are challenges in each level to provide replay value and incentive to experiment with setups.

Very Fun Game. I was always playing before work, after work and it seems well balanced. You can occasionally select your favorite characters and upgrade their abilities. Overall very fun. Spent lots of time playing it. A game well made.
Neat little strategy game
Outstanding Storyline & Gameplay. Loved every minute of it, even played on Hard level all throughout.

Infuriatingly unfair odds. Some may find this a fun challenge, but for me it was frustrating and felt more like torture. And skipping a level does not make it better, it only makes you feel like a dumbass. You play games to feel empowered and rewarded not to be reminded that you're an idiot. I get enough of that irl. Tone down the difficulty and I'll give it another go.
Nice game good buy !
Great game with good story,clever rpg/strategy elements. Very addictive
Amazing game concept and story!!

The only thing I didn't like about this game is that I finished it and now I want other games on this level and that's not gonna happen. This game is a unique standout on the mobile genre and it's one of the best I've ever played.
The first game I have finished on my phone in a long time.
Good solid game

One of the best games on Android. Polished, beautiful to look at, and has layers of strategy gradually introduced that keep it fresh and engaging. If you like tactical strategy, interesting and memorable characters, lots of customization with awesome abilities and weapon upgrades this one has you covered.
This is a really enjoyable tactical RPG. The one thing I think might extend it to a 5 star game is a branching story line where you need to make some choices about which path to take.

Takes a bit for it to pick up, but worthwhile. Skills & combat get pretty intricate and a lot of fun. The story ends up being very good & has good character arcs + development. Hope for sequel. Gameplay became too easy later on and needed a higher difficulty option. Rarer gems for augmenting were too sparse; no more than a few by the end of game could be made & only 1 in one case. Weapons were also too few & obtainable too early. There is also no replay value once you beat the game.

Excellent turn based strategy game which requires forthought. Chaining matching tiles to power up your attack and to collect them to use your abilities is a unique take on the genre. The only complaint I have is that sometimes it is difficult to target your character and move them along the path you want to with precision. Using a gamepad or a stylus can probably solve this problem though. Even thought I played this with Game Pass, this is one of the few mobile games that is worth buying.
Flecking perfection!

Not what i expected! The gritty comic-style storyline blends with the unique matching-puzzle/skill-tree game play in a very satisfying way. The dialog, graphics, and interface are as polished and pleasing as any of the best titles in my 300+ game Steam library. And, after a number of missions in, I expected to move on to the second of 4 chapters. I was happy to find there were many more missions yet to play. And with 0 ads/paywalls it is worth much more than they're asking.

Excellent, like playing through a RPG book, with great graphics and character development! No ads or in-app purchases made it truly enjoyable. Game mechanics are unique and interesting, with multi-layer strategy play. Each encounter you choose characters and powers to equip, and the abiity to 'visit the past' allows you to replay with different combinations. Leveling system for powers, weapons, and skills is intriguing. Sorry to reach the end, would love to see more from this talented team!
Don't get this game. It's addicting and it will ruin your life. I can't stop playing.
Really fun and interesting

This is such an amazing game!! I downloaded it because it had crazy positive reviews, but still was a bit skeptical. It is very simple to start and it progressively teaches you how to play through trial and error. It is a bit like the Tomb Raider Go and Hitman Go games but with RPG elements and much more strategy. Later in the game after building up your characters, the challenge sort of disappears. Other than that, this is a finally crafted strategy game.
I'm into it. All around a pretty entertaining game, no complaints yet. Play it.
Totally worth a play. Innovative, engaging, and impressive storyline. Kind of addictive...
Fun game no microtransactions.
This game is amazing and cool, looks like X Com but with little seasoning
Great game

Wow, just finished playing this little gem (which I found in Google Pass list). I would gladly pay for more games like this instead of junks with pay2win inside. Very good job, and I would love to play a sequel...

Exceptionally addictive and extensively well made game. Don't know why its cost is so low and why they haven't made more games. These people are wonderful developers and need a boost. Thank you for the lovely game.

This game was excellent! It had many hours of gameplay, is not overly complicated or frustrating, and had enough story to be interesting while at the same time not be intrusive or overbearing. I'd like to see a little more depth in character development and a larger variety of weapons, but what was there doesn't feel too limiting. I'd love to see more from this talented dev team.
Truly fantastic game
Great story and game play.
Exceptional game.
Fun and challenging game. Well made and good story so far.
Fun

replyContent: Sorry you are experiencing problems. You should not have to rebuy the game. This sounds like there may be an issue with Google Play Store data on your device. Perhaps try uninstalling Google Play Store updates, clearing the cache and data for Google Play Services and Google Play Store, restarting the device, and then reinstalling the game.

content: Such a great game!!! Exactly what I've been looking for. I just finished banner saga 1 and 2 (no 3 on Android, rip), and was looking for a similar game experience. This game has a unique art style that's plays out like a graphic novel between battles, and the combat itself is a unique mix of match three or whatever it's called and tactical combat. The "play board" is filled with types of certain colors which unlock certain powers or abilities unique to the characters in play. So much fun!

Such fantastic gameplay, and the story is decent, too. I would readily buy future games from the developer with this style of combat system. Easy to get used to and the format is short enough for a bus or cab ride. My only gripe is my finger doesn't always register right away when I press on a character, leading to a couple times when I've made a move I didn't intend to. Not frequent enough to be game breaking, but it's happened 6 or 7 times.

replyContent: If it's crashing at the logo, it may be the game wasn't given permissions to access its data file. At installation, it asks for permissions to access your media files. content: I just finished Episode 3, with 33/44 achievements unlocked. This is an excellent game! Fans of Banner Saga, XCOM will definitely enjoy this game.

Ticket to Earth's gameplay system (tile turned-based combat) is interesting but unfortunately the game goes from 0-100 in terms of difficulty fairly early in the game and because combat arena tile sets are completely random, I found myself constantly restarting missions just to get a not-so-stupidly-unfair tileset from the very first turn (i.e being limited to 2-3 tile movements since the patterns screw you over). Enemies seemingly random movement distances; one enemy that might have only been able to move 3-4 tiles in one mission is now capable of moving 10+ tiles the next mission. And the game puts barriers on progression if you are unable to beat either a main mission or a sidequest. So if you can't get past a mission, there's no means of grinding experience or currency for better skills; you simply have to get lucky with good tile sets.   If the difficulty curve revolves entirely around luck, its simply not fun. What a waste of a unique gameplay concept.
replyContent: Hi! In the early levels, try to play defensively. Keep your distance from the enemies (as they have a fixed movement range), avoid getting surrounded, and only attack when you can do significant damage. Ranged Combat Powers will also help. To practise TTE's combat, try the Rookie difficulty setting for a few levels. (You can switch back any time.)

Amazing game. Robot Circus got it way right. Incredible graphics, music, and gameplay. The puzzles are thought-provoking, but still keeps you in the RPG action. Meaningful choices makes the game continually interesting, and the story is great. There is also so much gameplay for the price, and I feel like we've finally started to turn a corner again predatory IAP--Robot Circus nails the value here. I will pay these prices all day for such great content. One note for completionists: this game has mission bonuses you will not be able to complete before the mission disappears. There is a mechanic to let you replay most missions for perfect scores, which is a necessity given you are often not powerful enough to get perfect mission scores right at the start. But some Justice Missions WILL disappear before you are powerful enough to complete them. Gotta just let it go.

You can play for just five minutes, or sit down play for hours. It auto saves with no punishment. The story is perfect for a mobile game -- it drives the game play without being too involved. My only two gripes are: a) There is no way to "farm" for more cash to upgrade skills outside of one-off missions. b) It seems to eat my battery life a little more than other mobile games I have played. All in all, a VERY solid game. You can't go wrong for $5! Bravo to the Robot Circus team! :) Edit 10/15/2018: A new update has arrived! I've been checking once a week and it's finally here! That's how excited I am for this game. Give these guys your $5, you won't regret it!
replyContent: Thanks for the kind words! If power drain is a problem ( and you don't mind limiting the game to 30FPS),  you could try the "30FPS Power Save" setting, from the main menu. It should help a bit.

I like. Missions are kinda shorts, which is perfectly suitable for a cell 
phone game. Yet they can be quite challengy. I have nothing to say on the

unfinished with no sign of a completion date
Simple to learn, hard to master turn-based strategy game. Great (as far as quality) and quite grimm (as far as content) story. Love the graphical style. Well worth the price. Please, more like this.

It's kind of difficult to put into so many words what I like and don't like about this game.  It's certainly not a strategy RPG (at least not in the normal sense), But neither can it be called an Action RPG.   I don't like strategy RPGs on account that I find their difficulty to be rather steep. THIS game, on the other hand seems a lot more aproachable for me then.  Still, the difficulty curve isn,t quite as smooth as I would like it to be. (Of course, it may also just be that I suck at these kinds of games in general)   Tokens to unlock new abilities are more difficut than I would like. Justice tokens take a long time to collect and their effectiveness makes me question the effort. The same could be said about Nitrium shards.  On the other hand, its nice to across a game in the Play Store that has an actual story with meat! The sound and music aren't bad either.  Of course, I find it disappointing after completing the game that Episode 3 and 4 aren't ready yet. Maybe I will have reason to raise my rating after playing them.

An interesting tactical game. A few imperfections (slow start, writing could be better, and unbalanced characters) but it grows on you as you play (interesting story and characters, and interesting tactical options once you've played for a while)
Puzzle, turn based fighting for the win.
Great game. It is fun to play and original.
Great game, dark story! Worth playing as it has interesting game play mechanics, lovely graphics, good writing, no IAP or freemium BS. A proper game that is fun to play!

Very creative game. It is easy to understand how it works but hard to master(which is not a bad thing) . It can be complicated at times but entertaining at the same time. The use of the puzzle mechanics may sound simple but as long as you progress the game you will understand that you have to move strategically. The visuals are very colourful and they match with the grim-dark atmosphere. This Is one of the best games in the market and worth every cent.
Excellent game

Incredibly underrated game. Tactical turn-based mechanic is creative and gives space for a lot of strategic ingenuity and flexibility. Story is well-written and moves quickly, with interesting characters. Would love if art style during gameplay could match cutaways a little more but that's a very minor complaint. This should be at the top of Play Store charts!

Absolutely loved the game. But then I uninstalled it (and I hope my progress was saved somewhere). Kind of BS to release a game half done. I mean I already paid for the full game but there's no guarantees I'm ever going to get it. So I'm just going to stop now before I star caring too much. Let me know when the game is complete.

A great game in desperate need of a difficulty setting. On act two, and cannot get far as enemies are so mobile I get swamped within a few turns. Enemy damage doesn't seem to rely on path distance. Please just add a difficulty level.
Great and fun little rpg. Great for gaming on the go

This game provides an engaging anti-capitalist narrative, as the wealthy corporate rulers of your mining planet prepare to escape the consequences of their ruthless resource extraction and labor exploitation.
I suck at this game.  Once the Jamais breaks loosetent it's impossible to pass any level.
Such a fun game! Love the tactics, it can be difficult sometimes and you learn from your mistakes.
Incredible! Very entertaining and addictive. Great storyline.
Compelling characters, engaging story, and a wholly unique game play style makes it better than 95% of  games you'll find on the store.
One of the best games I ever played on a mobile platform
Very unique from all of the mobile games I've played. Great story thus far and a nice mixture of strategy and difficulty. I love that there are no IAPs after purchasing the game. Great game!
Really high quality game. Very enjoyable, too short (but more's coming). Excellent writing/story. Totally worth the money. Highly complex srpg/puzzle game.
nicely made...

Original game mechanic, fun and challenging.  Only negative side, the story is a bit blend and deja-vu, a hero who don't want to be one fighting against super evil dudes and corporations with a corrupt government.

Definitely worth trying! Addictive, without any form of ads, in-app purchases and forced wait times! Cool system and a nice story filled with subtle jokes makes me compare this with respect to full games on Steam üòÅ
A wonderfully inventive game with beautiful visuals and a surprising amount of depth, in story and gameplay. Can't wait for the next chapter!

Really enjoy this game. Simple concept with a good amount of depth. I played it every day on my long train rides to and from work until I wound up running into end of content, having also 100%'d every mission. Waiting for the next chapter! Absolutely worth the few bucks to buy the game!
Fantastic game. Worth every cent!
Awesome take on a well-worn concept. I love the RPG elements, and the lack of pay2win.
Excellent turn based strategy with a clever core mechanic that forces movement. Highly recommended!
The new crack cant wait for eps 3 and 4!
Under priced gem, continues the trend of outstanding games coming from Down Under in the last few years. The future shines bright for these devs.
Badass game alert!   Hidden gem alert!   This game is unique goodness and well worth the money and some extra.   I await a sequel or downloadable content.
A unique combination of casual puzzle-solving and turn-based combat. Top-notch Android port, just as good as the iOS version.
such a fun game with an intricate storyline! I am obsessed!

This game is an excellent fusion of puzzle and turned based combat. The art style, story, and presentation is unique. After paying the $5 price of admission you recieve the entire game with no ads or IAPs. The developers are also releaseing episode 3 and 4 for no charge. Fantastic game, its worth every penny! My only complaint is the game was released on iOS first and we had to wait on Andriod.
Every thing  is great. Challenging, good story, great graphics and fun game play
I will have to reiterate all the good reviews of others. This is a brilliant game. A diamond in the rough if you will thank you to the developers of this fine masterpiece of a game. Again thank you.
Excellent strategy game
Very addictive and easy to grasp gameplay. I just can't stop coming back to this game. Amazing!

replyContent: The content for Ticket to Earth is being released episodically, and Episodes 3 and 4 will be available as free updates. We will be announcing more information about Episode 3's release soon.

content: Challenging puzzles. Good story.
Wow this is a total hidden gem. Great implementation of puzzle RPG, great production all around.
Best thing since puzzle quest.
Good strategy game with RPG components. Took me about 11 hours to end episode 2, which is the ending of the game thus far. I hope I can keep my progress for the upcoming episodes.

Definitely one of the best mobile games I've played for a while. Similar to the original puzzle quest the developers took a well known puzzle mechanic and added a great battle mechanic as well as a good story. I'm not the biggest fan of the comic graphics used in the dialogs but the rest of the game definitely makes up for it.

Such a solid game.  Combines the best parts of turn based strategy combat and puzzle mechanics.  Creative setting, engaging and deep characters.  Just really overall well crafted.  Was worth every penny.
Great turn based/puzzle game. Refreshing lack of IAP and really a full fledged experience that doesn't feel cramped on a phone.

Turn based tactics with a light puzzle aspect that keeps the grid maps interesting. Nicely thought out world with a decent story. No in app purchases. This was well worth it and is probably one of the best games I've found for Android.

Oh my god this is so addictive. Saw it at PAX and couldn't wait for the release on Android. The difficulty at the beginning is a really good challenge and when you start having powers it goes super smoothly. Can't wait for the next chapters :p
Incredible.   Three match game meets x com
Acceptable
This is just a really fun unique game

Great fun...... At first..... Then the difficulty starts ramping up at an absurd rate.
replyContent: Thanks for playing. In the earlier part of the game, position is really important. Avoid getting surrounded by enemies even if it means you can't attack that turn. Also, the robots have a limited movement range, so try to finish turns a few tiles away from them. After you get Combat Powers and the Talent Terminal, you'll get more ways to fight.

content: Controls are not always responsive, gameplay is linear, but tactical battles are lot of fun

Good stuff! I love the battle mechanics, which are fairly unique (as far as I know) and play well. The only real complaint I have is that the randomized tile-setting at the beginning of each mission can make for some pretty wide variation in your first turn effectiveness. A minor niggle, in the grand scheme of things. A fun game overall, and easily worth the purchase price.

Very impressive. Great story with interesting characters, top notch and innovative gameplay, crisp graphics and it's fun to boot.  This might be the best game I've ever played on a mobile platform. I think I got this as part of the launch sale, but whatever they are now asking for it, it's well worth it 10/10. Good work Devs, I hope this makes you some serious money, because I want you to make more games. I'll be watching Robot Circus closely.
replyContent: Thank you very much for playing our game, and thanks for the encouragement and support!! We definitely want to make more games too!

content: Surprisingly addictive. The gameplay is strategic (closest game I can think of is chess). Dialogue is good. Pretty PG but the plot is quite dark. Nice Aussie reference to the miners. ROFL

Very polished, unique game. The battle system is very cool and makes for the perfect mobile game. Though, I do wish there was a slightly better way to cancel unwanted path swipes. And, multi-kill objectives on early levels before you can even do multi-kills is frustrating.
replyContent: Thanks very much for playing and thank you for the review! To help with canceling paths, you can try out the "Confirm Move" option in the in-level pause menu. When that is enabled, the game will ask you to confirm the path before the characters move on it. That option can make it easier to cancel paths. Try it out and see if you prefer it.

content: Great game, but it's a little too easy to accidentally make moves you didn't intend to.
replyContent: Thanks very much for the review! To help avoid accidental moves, try out the "Confirm Move" option. You can activate it in the in-level pause menu. It can help with accidental moves, and also makes it easier to cancel a drawn line.

content: So innovative, it's new in its genre
Hybrid of puzzle and RPG. Story is keeping me engaged. Characters are interesting. No iaps, no pay to win. This game is awesome, thank you Devs.

Really fun game. Graphics are great; controls can be tricky sometimes e.g. it sometimes detects a tiny swipe instead of a tap. Dev Pune me in the direction of the in-level pause menu to turn the "confirm move" option on!
replyContent: Thanks very much for the kind words!!  Have you tried the "Confirm Move" option? You can switch this on from the in-level pause menu. If you turn this on, the game will ask you to confirm before the characters move on the line drawn. This provides an easier way to cancel a drawn line.

content: Gives you bonus objectives to get multiple kills in one turn before you get AoE skills and some levels are unbeatable.  Fail
replyContent: Hi there, the bonus objectives are not all intended to be completed in a single play. Some require the level to be revisited after the characters have levelled up or gained additional powers. A feature to replay missions unlocks after a few missions to enable you do this. You will be able to complete all objectives and get 100%. Hope this helps!

content: Awesome..no IAPS

This game will not launch on my Nexus 5X - never gets past the Robot Circus initial logo screen. Will happily update / remove review if I'm refunded or the issue is fixed.
replyContent: Hi there, the game should work on the 5X. This sounds like either the app wasn't given permissions to read its external data file during installation, or something else went wrong during the installation. Please confirm that the app has Storage permissions enabled. If that doesn't fix it, please delete the game & try reinstalling from Google Play.

content: Its a fun game, which combines puzzle and RPG mechanics, with a decent story line. Its more complicated the the likes of puzzle quest, but not that hard overall. The graphics are cell-shaded comic style. I've only played it for an hour so far, but I woul say it has a bunch of replayability. No ads, no in-app purchases. Its worth your time.
Played it already on IOS and loved it. Excellent value for the price and no f2p nonsense to ruin a great game. Instant buy as I noticed it's out on android.

Just a great game! I don't usually enjoy turn based gameplay, but the puzzle aspect of this game makes it really fun. I've been pretty addicted to this since I started playing. It's just challenging enough to keep you interested, without getting frustrated. The storyline is great, and the artwork is awesome. Nice job folks!
